1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,680
Good morning. Welcome. I appreciate you being here on a holiday weekend as this. I hope it's been fun and relaxing. It will continue to be as of tomorrow.

2
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:13,560
But I also have to announce one more meeting. This is kind of one of those quick things that has to happen.

3
00:00:14,060 --> 00:00:21,320
But I want to call a quick council meeting after the second service, after the Sunday school hour, to discuss again this property across the street.

4
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:25,580
And so for those who are on our administrative council, probably a 15-20 minute meeting.

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:31,940
I'd like for Jay Kramer, if you'd come, and also Ron Stevens, just for a few minutes, if we can do that, just to get a report back on what's doing over there.

6
00:00:33,340 --> 00:00:39,400
Well, it's a pleasure to begin, like I said, the unofficial end of summer.

7
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:41,820
Can you believe it? We're already into fall.

8
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:45,920
David Paye is already talking about Christmas music. I'm not quite ready to talk about that.

9
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:48,600
But that's how fast things roll. Here we go.

10
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:54,140
As you know, and maybe you haven't heard, I want to share, I'm starting a new series next week.

11
00:00:54,140 --> 00:01:03,840
And it's important that we be able to share effectively and defend the faith in the face of questions that are difficult.

12
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:08,480
Sometimes even for believers, we may believe and have experience with Christ,

13
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:14,820
and yet there's still these lingering questions that have never been really adequately dealt with or answered.

14
00:01:15,020 --> 00:01:16,960
And so that's our challenge this fall.

15
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:22,520
For the next eight weeks starting next week, we're going to do a series called Tough Questions and Honest Answers.

16
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:25,220
And we're basing it out of Lee Strobel's book,

17
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:27,260
the author who is speaking in just a couple weeks,

18
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,200
over at Biola.

19
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:30,620
If you want to get kind of an intro to that series,

20
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:33,940
go to that lecture, read the book, The Case for Faith,

21
00:01:33,940 --> 00:01:36,040
and we're going to be exploring those issues

22
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,620
from a biblical and philosophical standpoint

23
00:01:38,620 --> 00:01:42,020
and really defending what about these tough issues.

24
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,740
Why is there suffering and evil?

25
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:48,080
What about all the deaths of all the people in the Old Testament

26
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,420
that really put off people?

27
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:50,680
How can God be loving?

28
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:53,060
and still there's all this carnage.

29
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,480
That's a tough question.

30
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:56,280
What about science and miracles?

31
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,580
Are those contradictory?

32
00:01:57,860 --> 00:01:59,280
And all those kinds of issues.

33
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,520
We're going to talk biblically through each one.

34
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:02,600
I invite you to come.

35
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:05,220
This will be a bring your friend kind of series.

36
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,680
You've got friends ask you hard questions

37
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,340
and you're not sure?

38
00:02:09,250 --> 00:02:11,090
Say, I don't know, but come and hear my pastor

39
00:02:11,090 --> 00:02:12,470
and he's going to try and answer those.

40
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:13,890
And so you bring them the next eight weeks.

41
00:02:13,950 --> 00:02:15,570
I guarantee it will be a stimulating

42
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:17,150
and thought-provoking time.

43
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:18,870
We look forward to having you as part of that.

44
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:24,920
Well, as we now jump into this message on communion, we talked last week about the power

45
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:25,440
of symbols.

46
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:31,000
We talked about how in a symbol it can point to a deep reality that is difficult perhaps

47
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:37,530
to communicate in words, but the symbol itself can touch our souls in deep and powerful places.

48
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:43,130
And so I want to touch on the Lord's Supper, like we talked about baptism the previous

49
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:47,370
week. In taking the Lord's Supper, which we're going to do

50
00:02:47,370 --> 00:02:51,170
after this message, there's a symbolic action that really

51
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:55,110
cuts to the heart of the Gospel, and the Lord can teach us

52
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:58,810
and minister to us through the taking of these elements.

53
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:03,310
As we talked about last week, baptism is a once-for-all

54
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:07,290
experience that kind of marks our entering into new life with

55
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:10,430
Jesus. But the Lord's Supper, the communion meal,

56
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:13,530
instead is an ongoing experience

57
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:15,590
that we partake in on a regular basis.

58
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:19,890
And it really talks about the sustaining of our life in Christ.

59
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:23,070
Baptism is kind of the entrance symbolically,

60
00:03:23,830 --> 00:03:26,430
but communion is the ongoing nurture

61
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:29,690
and sustaining of that relationship.

62
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:32,530
I'd like to draw your attention this morning

63
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:36,810
to a classic text on this topic of communion in the Lord's Supper.

64
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:38,950
It's found in 1 Corinthians 11.

65
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:42,310
It will be on the screen, a number of screens. We're going to read it.

66
00:03:42,830 --> 00:03:45,070
If you'd like to turn your Bibles, feel free to do so as well.

67
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:49,370
1 Corinthians 11, starting in verse 17.

68
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:54,050
The Word of God says,

69
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:58,580
But now when I mention this next issue, Paul writes,

70
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:05,500
I cannot praise you, for it sounds as if more harm than good is done when you meet together.

71
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:10,470
First of all, I hear there are divisions among you when you meet as a church.

72
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:13,270
And to some extent, he says, I believe it.

73
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:16,170
But of course, there must be divisions among you

74
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:18,550
so that those of you who are right will be recognized.

75
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:21,970
It's not the Lord's Supper you're concerned about

76
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:22,870
when you come together.

77
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:26,090
For I'm told that some of you hurry to eat your own meal

78
00:04:26,090 --> 00:04:28,410
without sharing with others.

79
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:32,690
As a result, some go hungry while others get drunk.

80
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:35,630
What? Is this really true?

81
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:38,490
Don't you have your own homes for eating and drinking?

82
00:04:38,490 --> 00:04:41,550
or do you really want to disgrace the church of God

83
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:42,690
and shame the poor?

84
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:45,850
What am I supposed to say about these things?

85
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,750
Do you want me to praise you?

86
00:04:48,490 --> 00:04:50,390
Well, I certainly do not.

87
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,560
For this is what the Lord himself said,

88
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,480
and I pass it on to you just as I received it.

89
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,400
On the night when he was betrayed,

90
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,700
the Lord Jesus took a loaf of bread

91
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,320
and when he had given thanks,

92
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:03,700
he broke it and said,

93
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,700
this is my body which is given for you.

94
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:09,900
Do this in remembrance of me.

95
00:05:10,890 --> 00:05:13,630
In the same way, he took the cup of wine after supper, saying,

96
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:17,430
This cup is the new covenant between God and you,

97
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:19,650
sealed by the shedding of my blood.

98
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:24,450
Do this in remembrance of me, as often as you drink it.

99
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:27,630
For every time you eat this bread and drink this cup,

100
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:30,910
you are announcing the Lord's death until he comes.

101
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:33,040
And then he goes on.

102
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:37,240
So if anyone eats this bread or drinks this cup of the Lord unworthily,

103
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:41,340
That person is guilty of sinning against the body and the blood of our Lord.

104
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:45,520
That is why you should examine yourself before eating the bread and drinking from the cup.

105
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:50,380
For if you eat the bread or drink the cup unworthily, not honoring the body of Christ,

106
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:54,100
you are eating and drinking God's judgment upon yourself.

107
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:58,180
That is why many of you are weak and sick, and some have even died.

108
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:03,300
But if we examine ourselves, we will not be examined by God and judged in this way.

109
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:07,980
But when we are judged and disciplined by the Lord, we will not be condemned with the world.

110
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:13,040
So, dear brothers and sisters, when you gather for the Lord's Supper, wait for each other.

111
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:18,720
And if you are really hungry, eat at home so you won't bring judgment upon yourselves when you meet together.

112
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:23,660
I'll give you instructions about the other matters after I arrive.

113
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:32,900
To understand this text on communion, we've got to unpack this passage a little bit.

114
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,780
I want to get into the background for a moment.

115
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:39,900
So as we read this other person's mail, we're going to understand it more deeply.

116
00:06:40,260 --> 00:06:44,320
Paul is writing, as you may have gathered, to a church that had divisions.

117
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:48,060
That sounds like most churches I know in America, which is kind of sad,

118
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:52,360
but there's some deeper, really rife issues in this church.

119
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,780
And one in particular that Paul really is upset about

120
00:06:55,780 --> 00:07:00,040
is this issue between the rich Christians and the poor Christians

121
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:04,500
and how they were coming together and how those distinctions were exaggerated

122
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:08,780
and aggravated. The bottom line was that the minority of the

123
00:07:08,780 --> 00:07:12,840
wealthy believers, including the financial big backers of this

124
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:16,540
young church, were gathering in the homes of those who could

125
00:07:16,540 --> 00:07:21,040
afford homes. And they had the resources and the time to come

126
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:24,440
early to these festive meals. They had the opportunity to bring more

127
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:29,020
sensuous and temptuous and all those wonderful goodies. They could bring far

128
00:07:29,020 --> 00:07:33,730
greater offerings of food to the gathering. Those who

129
00:07:33,730 --> 00:07:40,070
came early, could enjoy gathering together in the private dining room. But the latecomers,

130
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:43,770
those who had to work in the various places, and by the way, they didn't have OSHA, they

131
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:48,930
didn't have the weekends off. I mean, when they got off work, which was every day, they

132
00:07:48,930 --> 00:07:52,750
finally could make it to the gathering. And they would come and they would be forced to

133
00:07:52,750 --> 00:08:00,570
sit in the atrium, kind of out in the other room. In the context of a meal that's supposed

134
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:05,140
to be about unity. There were divisions along socioeconomic

135
00:08:05,140 --> 00:08:09,370
lines. When the story gets worse, as you infer from

136
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:13,250
what Paul is saying, not only do they sit in separate rooms and we're not being

137
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:17,170
united, but the potluck people were gorging themselves

138
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:21,730
and the bottom line was some were getting drunk at the communion time.

139
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:27,690
Now realize this. Now Paul is not objecting to having a nice

140
00:08:27,690 --> 00:08:31,570
place to meet. He's not objecting to bringing wonderful delectables

141
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:33,070
to dine on together.

142
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:35,910
But what he's angry at and frustrated

143
00:08:35,910 --> 00:08:38,390
are these divisions between the rich and the poor

144
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:40,690
and the aggravation of those issues.

145
00:08:41,390 --> 00:08:43,190
And he's saying basically these are inappropriate.

146
00:08:43,450 --> 00:08:46,910
This is not how we celebrate the Lord's meal together.

147
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:50,670
And so I want us to understand those tensions as a background.

148
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,340
As we get into this passage, you'll see how they play out.

149
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,300
So with that in the back of our minds,

150
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:57,960
the first question I want to say is,

151
00:08:58,020 --> 00:09:00,340
well, what is the Lord's Supper?

152
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,320
What is the Lord's Supper?

153
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:06,630
First of all, it is a simple act.

154
00:09:08,350 --> 00:09:09,730
The Lord's Supper is a simple act.

155
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:11,830
It's not an elaborate ceremony.

156
00:09:12,310 --> 00:09:17,190
Notice how Paul documents what Jesus did when he first institutes this meal for us.

157
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:20,150
It says in 1 Corinthians 11, verse 23,

158
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:25,070
On the night he was betrayed, the Lord Jesus took a loaf of bread.

159
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:29,000
A common, everyday part of their meal together,

160
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,780
he took the loaf of bread.

161
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:34,980
Jesus was celebrating the Passover meal with his disciples.

162
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:37,680
During the Passover meal, just to give you some background,

163
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:42,660
the Jews ate unleavened bread to recall their departure out of Egypt.

164
00:09:42,820 --> 00:09:47,860
They're celebrating God's deliverance of the people from slavery in Egypt.

165
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:54,630
And the Passover was the experience of commemorating and remembering that historical event.

166
00:09:54,990 --> 00:09:57,090
And as was customary in doing that,

167
00:09:57,090 --> 00:10:04,110
The head of the household would stand and take the bread and talk about it and break it and so forth

168
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:09,050
and distribute it as part of that celebration of the Exodus event.

169
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:15,190
So Jesus, as head of the disciples, head leader and teacher of this band of followers,

170
00:10:15,570 --> 00:10:18,650
he stands and he divides the bread.

171
00:10:19,370 --> 00:10:22,690
But then Jesus gives new meaning to the bread.

172
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,060
And so my second point is this,

173
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,480
that the communion meal is a reminder,

174
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:29,640
it's a memory tool.

175
00:10:31,690 --> 00:10:34,550
Notice in 1 Corinthians now in verse 24, chapter 11,

176
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:37,840
And when he had given thanks, he broke it and he said,

177
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:41,150
This is my body which is given for you.

178
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:45,140
Do this in remembrance of me.

179
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:49,790
The same bread that was symbolic of the unleavened bread

180
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:52,390
that the Israelites ate on the way out of Egypt

181
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:58,530
is now by Jesus being designated as kind of a sacrificial body.

182
00:10:59,590 --> 00:11:02,290
You see, in the Old Testament, under the sacrificial system,

183
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:05,810
the animal victim of sacrifice was laid on the altar

184
00:11:05,810 --> 00:11:08,110
and the blood was poured out.

185
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:11,950
The death of the animal was to take away the sin of the people.

186
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:15,870
And now Jesus is beginning to bring that system into this meal

187
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:18,030
and re-designating these elements.

188
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:22,250
Notice in Isaiah 53, Jesus alludes to this passage.

189
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:26,600
I will give him the honors of one who is mighty and great,

190
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:29,260
because he exposed himself to death.

191
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:31,880
He was counted among those who were sinners.

192
00:11:32,380 --> 00:11:36,040
He bore the sins of many, and he interceded for sinners.

193
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,920
Isaiah 53 is a passage about the suffering servant

194
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:42,500
that would take away the sins of the people,

195
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:45,140
and Jesus is alluding now to that passage

196
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:48,140
coming into being through Jesus himself.

197
00:11:49,530 --> 00:11:51,890
Jesus' body was going to be given

198
00:11:51,890 --> 00:11:53,890
for those who were eating at that table.

199
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,950
Jesus' body is being given up

200
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:57,910
for all those who would follow.

201
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:00,840
And as part of that ritual, Jesus says,

202
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:04,400
do this in remembrance of me.

203
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,200
And so we take that to realize

204
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,480
that Jesus is saying to us,

205
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:10,420
this meal, this celebration, this event

206
00:12:10,420 --> 00:12:12,100
is to take place over and over

207
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,920
as a frequent experience

208
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:17,360
that we might remember what happened.

209
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:18,960
So number two, it's a reminder.

210
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,960
It's a memory tool.

211
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:26,410
And number three, communion, it's a symbol.

212
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,620
In verse 25, he continues,

213
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,990
in the same way he took the cup of wine after supper,

214
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:33,650
and he's saying,

215
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:37,430
this cup is the new covenant between God and you,

216
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,210
sealed by the shedding of my blood.

217
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:43,870
Do this in remembrance of me as often as you drink it.

218
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:47,090
When Jesus is talking about the bread,

219
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:49,530
when Jesus is talking about the wine and the cup,

220
00:12:50,190 --> 00:12:52,290
the disciples would not have thought then

221
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:55,670
that he was somehow saying that this bread or this cup

222
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:57,290
was literally Jesus' body.

223
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,490
They would see him as making an analogy,

224
00:13:00,190 --> 00:13:03,930
a representation of his coming bodily death.

225
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:08,250
And I want to also point out the symbolism behind the cup.

226
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:11,330
You notice that Jesus doesn't say necessarily this wine.

227
00:13:11,430 --> 00:13:15,130
He talks about this cup as he's grabbing some kind of chalice.

228
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:19,190
But see, the word cup is used over and over in the Old Testament

229
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:22,810
to refer to wrath that God is going to pour out.

230
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:26,970
Example 51.7, 17 in Isaiah.

231
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:29,970
Awake, awake, rise, O Jerusalem,

232
00:13:31,030 --> 00:13:32,910
you who have drunk from the hand of the Lord

233
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:34,940
the cup of his wrath,

234
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,420
you who have drained to its dregs

235
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:39,380
the goblet that makes men stagger.

236
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:42,770
You see, Jesus pointing to the cup

237
00:13:42,770 --> 00:13:45,530
and pointing to the fact that he

238
00:13:45,530 --> 00:13:49,610
would be taking on the wrath of God

239
00:13:49,610 --> 00:13:50,390
that we deserve.

240
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:54,550
When he talks about the covenant

241
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:56,760
and the shedding of blood.

242
00:13:57,860 --> 00:14:00,980
Jesus making an allusion to Exodus 24,

243
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,880
whereby in this old covenant where God is saying,

244
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:07,500
you will be my people and I will be your God, essentially,

245
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,220
and that the people are going to do these things

246
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:12,140
to be in a covenant community with God,

247
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:14,820
that the blood was sprinkled on the people.

248
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,760
Notice Exodus chapter 24.

249
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,960
And Moses took the book of the covenant

250
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,940
and read it to the people.

251
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,020
And they all responded again.

252
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,520
We will do everything the Lord has commanded.

253
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:25,980
we will obey.

254
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,960
And then Moses sprinkled the blood from the basins

255
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,320
over the people and he said,

256
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,980
this blood confirms the covenant of the Lord

257
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:36,420
is made with you in giving you these laws.

258
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:40,260
Symbolic language Jesus uses

259
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:42,760
to communicate the great truths

260
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,540
about his upcoming passion,

261
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,140
about his going to the cross,

262
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:49,020
about his becoming the sacrificial lamb

263
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:51,840
for all of us once and for all.

264
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:55,190
And the wine of the cup

265
00:14:55,190 --> 00:14:58,410
signifying Jesus' blood being poured out

266
00:14:58,410 --> 00:15:00,420
for the new covenant.

267
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:04,350
The new covenant, like the old covenant with Israel,

268
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:07,710
is not a contract between two equal parties,

269
00:15:08,290 --> 00:15:11,070
but it's an offer made by God to human beings,

270
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:13,870
people that could not save themselves.

271
00:15:14,490 --> 00:15:15,810
It's an offer of pardon.

272
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,140
It's an offer of power.

273
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:21,760
It's an offer that we can only freely accept

274
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:24,790
with gratitude and with faith.

275
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:29,050
And my next point, number four, is communion then.

276
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:32,890
is a statement of faith.

277
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,480
Moving on now in verse 26,

278
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:39,330
Paul continues to write that Jesus said,

279
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:43,400
For every time you eat this bread and drink this cup,

280
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:47,460
you are announcing the Lord's death until he comes.

281
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:51,320
You see, communion, this celebration we're about to take,

282
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:54,860
is not simply a memorial meal of Jesus' last supper.

283
00:15:55,340 --> 00:15:58,280
It's not just a remembrance of the Lord's death

284
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:01,960
for the sake of our remembering a painful historical event.

285
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:04,380
Instead, communion is a remembrance

286
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:08,640
and a remembering of what Jesus' death does for us,

287
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,840
for now, and for our future.

288
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,380
You see, there's a future.

289
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:16,900
There's an end times reality to the Lord's Supper.

290
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:20,700
For we Christians, we have not arrived yet.

291
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:26,340
We're not done being made and shaped by the Holy Spirit.

292
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:29,800
We're not ready yet to meet our Lord face to face.

293
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,020
but he's making us ready.

294
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:33,720
And the communion meal points to the reality

295
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:37,560
that we will one day see Jesus face to face forever.

296
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:40,290
That is our hope.

297
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,670
Because of what happened at the cross,

298
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,170
we'll be with God forever.

299
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,380
It's a statement of faith.

300
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:51,920
Now I want to move into this dimension of,

301
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:53,840
well then, who should take the Lord's Supper?

302
00:16:53,940 --> 00:16:55,120
My second major point.

303
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:57,440
Who should take this meal?

304
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:03,820
I've noticed in the scriptures that Jesus had this meal.

305
00:17:04,810 --> 00:17:07,050
Not with all the crowds that followed him.

306
00:17:07,270 --> 00:17:09,210
There were many crowds that followed Jesus.

307
00:17:09,890 --> 00:17:13,710
But the disciples were the one that got to partake of communion with Jesus.

308
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:18,480
I see Jesus having communion with those that were intimate with him.

309
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:21,220
He gave it to his intimate believers.

310
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:26,640
And I discern from the text that the communion meal is really designated for those

311
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,900
who are professing Christians, who are saying,

312
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:32,480
Yes, Jesus is my Lord. He is my Savior.

313
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,770
and I am following him.

314
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:37,840
I am a disciple and he is my Lord.

315
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:42,020
The great New Testament scholar Craig Blomberg

316
00:17:42,020 --> 00:17:44,380
out of Denver Seminary writes these powerful words

317
00:17:44,380 --> 00:17:45,880
in commenting on this text.

318
00:17:46,950 --> 00:17:49,410
He says, all repentant sinners are welcome,

319
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:51,090
referring to the Lord's table,

320
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:54,870
no matter how far away from God they may recently have felt.

321
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:58,190
All professing believers who are unprepared

322
00:17:58,190 --> 00:17:59,970
to give generously, though, of their wealth

323
00:17:59,970 --> 00:18:01,250
to help the poor in the midst

324
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:03,710
or who treat the people of lower classes

325
00:18:03,710 --> 00:18:07,490
as second citizens or simply remained unreconciled

326
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:10,150
should refrain from the meal.

327
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:15,260
All repentant sinners may come to the meal.

328
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:17,890
All repentant sinners.

329
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,300
I also want to point out that

330
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:24,000
whether you come from a different tradition,

331
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,940
sometimes I'll say it rather colloquially,

332
00:18:28,940 --> 00:18:31,900
what franchise of the church are you coming from?

333
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,480
Because we're all one united body,

334
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:37,040
different denominations, different traditions

335
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,780
that emphasize different practices.

336
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:40,180
But the bottom line is,

337
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:42,240
if we're professing Jesus as Lord and Savior,

338
00:18:42,620 --> 00:18:44,340
we are the one body of Christ.

339
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,720
If you're coming from a different tradition

340
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,960
and you are in our service and we're having communion,

341
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:51,280
you are welcome if you profess Jesus Christ

342
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:53,680
as Lord and as Savior.

343
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:57,680
Does one need to be baptized to receive communion?

344
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,800
I don't see that from the text.

345
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:04,280
I see baptism as simply expressing

346
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:05,920
what has already happened in your life.

347
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:08,210
And it's an obedience issue

348
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:09,410
and you should be baptized.

349
00:19:10,860 --> 00:19:11,920
But is it a precursor?

350
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,720
I can't make that connection necessarily.

351
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:17,070
Some traditions make that part of the process.

352
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,160
I would like to say that if children

353
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:23,060
who understand who Jesus is

354
00:19:23,060 --> 00:19:24,680
and are, yes, saying they are following,

355
00:19:25,820 --> 00:19:26,880
they may take communion.

356
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:28,460
If they have not been baptized yet,

357
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:31,820
I'm still open to them partaking of that experience,

358
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:34,040
though I want them to be baptized.

359
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:38,040
We've talked about the who.

360
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:40,500
Let's talk about the how.

361
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:46,060
As we said before, Jesus says, do this in remembrance of me.

362
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:51,180
The connotation there is that this experience is an ongoing kind of meal that we would take over and over.

363
00:19:52,130 --> 00:19:56,570
But it's interesting, he never did say particularly how we're to celebrate the Lord's Supper.

364
00:19:56,670 --> 00:19:59,750
There are no instructions other than what happened historically there.

365
00:20:00,290 --> 00:20:07,010
Now this church, we partake of this experience roughly one time per month on the first Sunday of the month

366
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:10,440
as a way of making it a special occasion

367
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,760
but still regular enough

368
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,240
that it's part of our worship year

369
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,420
on an ongoing basis.

370
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:16,950
And you'll notice in the text

371
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:19,330
there's no prescription for the form of communion.

372
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,620
One loaf of bread is accurate.

373
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:26,670
Unleavened bread that we use in cracker form

374
00:20:26,670 --> 00:20:29,510
grabs on the imagery of the unleavened bread

375
00:20:29,510 --> 00:20:30,450
coming out of Egypt.

376
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:33,250
Little cups are fine.

377
00:20:33,610 --> 00:20:35,030
A big goblet is fine.

378
00:20:35,130 --> 00:20:38,110
Different traditions will do it in different ways.

379
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:42,280
But I think an interesting issue does come up here.

380
00:20:43,580 --> 00:20:46,640
And I want to bring out verses 27 to 29.

381
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,430
Again, chapter 11.

382
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:55,750
So if anyone eats this bread or drinks this cup of the Lord unworthily,

383
00:20:56,110 --> 00:21:00,050
that person is guilty of sinning against the body and the blood of the Lord.

384
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:04,350
That is why you should examine yourself before eating the bread and drinking from the cup.

385
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:08,870
For if you eat the bread or drink the cup unworthily, not honoring the body of Christ,

386
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:11,870
you are eating and drinking God's judgment upon yourself.

387
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:14,010
And then he says, that's why many of you are weak and sick.

388
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:15,650
And some of you even died.

389
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:19,850
I want to come to this difficult word, unworthily.

390
00:21:20,650 --> 00:21:22,570
What does he mean by that?

391
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:27,140
The New International Version of the New American Standard Bible

392
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:30,120
translated in an unworthy manner.

393
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,210
What is Paul saying?

394
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:36,910
And the reason I make a lot about this particular word

395
00:21:36,910 --> 00:21:40,020
is because many have taken the reference there

396
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:43,500
to mean that if we are not absolutely right with the Lord,

397
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:48,440
if you have not made sure that every sin has been confessed and purged out of your life,

398
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:51,620
perhaps from that day or that week or that last month,

399
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:55,240
then somehow you are not worthy to take the Lord's Supper.

400
00:21:56,240 --> 00:22:01,600
And many have come and have not taken because of this issue of unworthily,

401
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:04,140
and they feel unworthy to partake.

402
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:09,440
But as I get into this text, and you get into the context of this text,

403
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:13,400
and you look at the grammar, I don't see unworthy used in that manner.

404
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:16,960
Remember again, Paul is writing to people

405
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,300
who are using the Lord's Supper

406
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:22,860
as a way to divide the church amongst rich and poor.

407
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:28,140
Remember that they're gorging themselves at the meal.

408
00:22:28,540 --> 00:22:30,680
Some are getting drunk at the meal.

409
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,080
It's a very different context

410
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,640
in which we celebrate it today.

411
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:37,190
But in that context,

412
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:40,780
instead of Paul attacking the person's character

413
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:42,140
or sin issues,

414
00:22:42,140 --> 00:22:47,180
He's attacking their behavior towards other believers in their body.

415
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:51,780
He's challenging their socioeconomic aggravation of those issues.

416
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:58,130
They ate the meal in an unworthy manner.

417
00:22:58,130 --> 00:23:03,970
They ate the meal in contradistinction to how Jesus wants to be celebrated in unity.

418
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,760
They're exasperating the differences.

419
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,890
And they're eating in an unworthy manner.

420
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:15,880
What they're doing contradicts what Jesus is trying to communicate

421
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:18,140
and what he did on the cross in bringing unity to believers.

422
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:20,460
We're all one family.

423
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:23,730
They were dividing the family.

424
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:30,800
Examine here, the literal word has the idea of test and find approved.

425
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:34,640
If their behavior towards their fellow Christians is appropriate,

426
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:38,200
then they are qualified to come and partake of the meal.

427
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:40,920
This is not one of those ultra-pietistic,

428
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:44,460
I've got to figure out how my soul is doing every moment.

429
00:23:44,780 --> 00:23:50,780
The issue is, are their actions and attitude towards others consistent with the reality of the body of Christ?

430
00:23:51,610 --> 00:23:54,270
That's the issue in this text.

431
00:23:54,710 --> 00:23:58,590
And if they are not, if they're holding bitterness towards the poor Christians,

432
00:23:58,830 --> 00:24:01,630
or the poorer Christians are holding bitterness towards the rich Christians,

433
00:24:01,870 --> 00:24:04,970
if there's bitterness and there's angst and anger and all those things,

434
00:24:05,230 --> 00:24:07,630
then they are guilty of the body and the blood.

435
00:24:07,630 --> 00:24:16,140
it. They, in a sense, are sinning, and that kind of sin is what's liable for Jesus' death. I see

436
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:22,400
communion, friends, as a reminder of the reality of Jesus' death and the hope that we have in new

437
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:28,810
life that it points to. And if a person is a Christian, and yet that person has some sin in

438
00:24:28,810 --> 00:24:33,090
their life, they're struggling with something, or perhaps they've made a gross error that morning

439
00:24:33,090 --> 00:24:41,060
of that week in God's eyes. I want them to take communion. I want them to come back as a reminder,

440
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:47,520
a memory tool. This is what reality is. And I want them to repent of that experience, of course,

441
00:24:47,780 --> 00:24:55,530
but we're already all unworthy to take because of our sin anyway. I don't want the communion meal

442
00:24:55,530 --> 00:25:01,510
to be missed because of sin. I want the communion meal to convince and challenge and reorient their

443
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:10,270
lives, that they may not sin anymore. It's a way for people to come and get a grip again

444
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:16,840
on their faith, on the commitments they've made to follow Christ. I want them to take

445
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:28,020
communion. I want it to be a reorienting of their soul. Verse 29, for if you eat the bread

446
00:25:28,020 --> 00:25:31,440
or drink the cup unworthily, not honoring the body of Christ, you're eating and drinking

447
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:38,880
God's judgment upon yourself. He says not honoring the body of Christ. Body. What does

448
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:47,000
you mean by that? I think, and most contemporary scholars today look at this, when he says

449
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:53,780
body there in verse 29, he is referring to the corporate body of Christ. Not necessarily

450
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:59,720
to Jesus' body, but referring to the body of Christ, the church. Those who eat and drink

451
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:07,000
in flagrant disregard for the body of Christ and its unity, they are the ones incurring

452
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:11,680
the risk of judgment from God. I like how the CEV, Contemporary English Version, puts

453
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,420
this. Would you show that version, please?

454
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:15,680
Verse 29. If you

455
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,320
fail to understand, it says,

456
00:26:17,620 --> 00:26:19,620
that you are the body of the

457
00:26:19,620 --> 00:26:21,830
Lord, you will condemn yourselves

458
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:23,840
by the way you eat and by the

459
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:26,500
way you drink. The NIV

460
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:28,940
translation saying body of the Lord, I think

461
00:26:28,940 --> 00:26:30,740
is a little bit off. The older

462
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:32,160
manuscripts don't show it that way.

463
00:26:34,940 --> 00:26:36,740
Friends, we come to the Lord's Supper. We are

464
00:26:36,740 --> 00:26:38,640
to discern that we are

465
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,660
one body of Christ, rich and

466
00:26:40,660 --> 00:26:42,500
poor, different socioeconomic

467
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:46,280
classes, different races, different populations. We are unified

468
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:50,440
in Jesus Christ, different languages, different tongues, nations, you name it.

469
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:53,720
We all are united in Jesus Christ.

470
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:58,500
And if we're abusing those sociological status

471
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:02,740
and all of those things, then we are incurring judgment of the Lord.

472
00:27:02,740 --> 00:27:05,660
And Paul then says in verse 30, I put that up there,

473
00:27:06,900 --> 00:27:09,500
that is why many of you are weak and sick, and some have even died.

474
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:15,470
Paul has had it revealed to him by God supernaturally

475
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:19,950
that some of the sickness and the death that's been occurring in that community

476
00:27:19,950 --> 00:27:23,330
in the church community is a result of God's judgment upon them

477
00:27:23,330 --> 00:27:27,730
but I want us to be very careful now in how we apply that verse

478
00:27:27,730 --> 00:27:31,900
because it's easy to start thinking, well wait a minute, I'm sick, I've had

479
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:36,680
some chronic problem and maybe I'm part of this. I don't think we can say

480
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:40,600
necessarily that that situation translates into today directly

481
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:44,800
as when Paul was writing at that moment. Paul is talking about a situation

482
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:48,120
and a group of people, and I want to be very careful

483
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:54,640
in applying that today. But I would like to say this in conclusion.

484
00:27:57,520 --> 00:28:01,810
How the Lord's Supper is to be taken, we see nothing

485
00:28:01,810 --> 00:28:06,230
from the text that necessarily says that you have to have a Master of Divinity

486
00:28:06,230 --> 00:28:09,310
and an ordination certificate to preside.

487
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,220
Though I do think there's something to that

488
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:14,220
in terms of the order of the church

489
00:28:14,220 --> 00:28:17,040
and in having people in that status doing that.

490
00:28:17,140 --> 00:28:18,340
But when they are not available,

491
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,540
I think it's appropriate for other leaders in the church

492
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:21,760
to dispense those things.

493
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:24,760
I don't see anything in the text that argues against

494
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:28,380
why women cannot distribute and serve communion as well.

495
00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,190
I want to summarize this.

496
00:28:32,930 --> 00:28:34,370
The theology of the Lord's Supper,

497
00:28:34,470 --> 00:28:36,570
I pull this out of Craig Blomberg again.

498
00:28:37,810 --> 00:28:38,630
I think it's well done.

499
00:28:38,690 --> 00:28:40,010
And these slides are going to go fast,

500
00:28:40,050 --> 00:28:40,990
so kind of watch them.

501
00:28:42,380 --> 00:28:45,440
But the Lord's Supper, the meaning underneath it all is this.

502
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:49,020
It looks back to Christ's death.

503
00:28:49,580 --> 00:28:51,060
It's a reminder, the memory tool.

504
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,680
It's an opportunity to look in and say,

505
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:57,460
how is my heart, how am I treating my fellow believers?

506
00:28:58,890 --> 00:28:59,930
Self-examination.

507
00:29:00,790 --> 00:29:03,830
It's an upward look to fellowship with God.

508
00:29:03,830 --> 00:29:05,550
Because of the death of Jesus,

509
00:29:05,710 --> 00:29:08,950
we have intimate connection and fellowship with God.

510
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:10,680
It's a look around.

511
00:29:11,890 --> 00:29:13,750
These are my brothers and sisters in Christ.

512
00:29:13,890 --> 00:29:15,630
We come together united to celebrate.

513
00:29:17,020 --> 00:29:20,040
We look forward to Christ's return,

514
00:29:20,860 --> 00:29:22,700
to the reality that we'll be with him forever.

515
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:27,280
And we look outward to proclaim God's word,

516
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:29,320
to proclaim the reality of this meal

517
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:32,960
and the truths behind it to the world at large

518
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:37,100
that needs to hear what God has done for us.

519
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,520
And finally, I just want to make this comment

520
00:29:41,520 --> 00:29:46,960
that we at this church, we on a monthly basis,

521
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:50,040
take what we call the Deacon's Fund offering.

522
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,080
It's something we take on Communion Sundays,

523
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:55,780
and I realize some of you may have already given to that experience.

524
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:58,540
I'm just going to kind of impromptu here.

525
00:29:58,620 --> 00:30:00,140
I would like to have our ushers in a moment.

526
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,520
After we have Communion,

527
00:30:02,350 --> 00:30:04,710
I'd like for us to take another offering

528
00:30:04,710 --> 00:30:07,390
specifically for our Deacon's Fund.

529
00:30:07,390 --> 00:30:08,890
And you may have already given to that,

530
00:30:09,010 --> 00:30:10,350
but for those who don't know about that,

531
00:30:10,410 --> 00:30:13,730
I want to just make it available to you one more time today.

532
00:30:14,130 --> 00:30:15,170
What we do here is this.

533
00:30:15,170 --> 00:30:18,850
for those who are hurting or have a financial crisis

534
00:30:18,850 --> 00:30:20,930
or a need or something comes up in their life.

535
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:23,810
We take certain funds on a monthly basis

536
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:27,150
for the needy and for those who are struggling.

537
00:30:28,250 --> 00:30:30,230
And the staff and the deacon team,

538
00:30:30,390 --> 00:30:32,370
we disperse those on a needed basis.

539
00:30:32,910 --> 00:30:34,610
And it comes out of this text,

540
00:30:34,990 --> 00:30:37,810
whereby the rich and the poor were united together

541
00:30:37,810 --> 00:30:39,550
and were taking care of each other's needs.

542
00:30:40,290 --> 00:30:42,970
And so on Communion Sunday, we take this offering.

543
00:30:43,710 --> 00:30:44,950
And again, if you've already given to this,

544
00:30:44,950 --> 00:30:46,110
I'm not asking you to do it again.

545
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:48,230
But for those who didn't know about that experience,

546
00:30:48,330 --> 00:30:49,530
what the Deacons Fund is all about,

547
00:30:49,590 --> 00:30:50,550
and if you'd like to contribute,

548
00:30:50,930 --> 00:30:54,110
it only goes for those as part of our church family

549
00:30:54,110 --> 00:30:55,550
that have a need.

550
00:30:56,450 --> 00:30:58,810
And the church uses those funds to do that.

551
00:30:58,850 --> 00:31:00,870
So after communion, I'd like to call the ushers forward again,

552
00:31:00,910 --> 00:31:01,930
and we'll just take that offering

553
00:31:01,930 --> 00:31:03,570
if you'd like to participate.

554
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:07,110
Well, now at this time, we've studied through the text

555
00:31:07,110 --> 00:31:07,950
the Lord's Supper.

556
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:11,640
It's now time that we partake.

